\section{ Introduction}
\index{Direct current}
\index{DC}
 

"DC" stands for \textbf{D}irect \textbf{C}urrent, which can refer to either voltage or current in a constant polarity or direction, respectively.  These experiments are designed to introduce you to several important concepts of electricity related to DC circuits.
 


\vfil \eject 

\section{ Series batteries}
\index{Experiment: Series batteries}
 

\textbf{PARTS AND MATERIALS}
 

\begin{itemize}
\item Two 6-volt batteries
\item One 9-volt battery
\end{itemize}
 

Actually, any size batteries will suffice for this experiment, but it is recommended to have at least two different voltages available to make it more interesting.
 

\bigskip 
 

\textbf{CROSS-REFERENCES}
 

 

\textit{Lessons In Electric Circuits}, Volume 1, chapter 5: "Series and Parallel Circuits"
 

 

\textit{Lessons In Electric Circuits}, Volume 1, chapter 11: "Batteries and Power Systems"
 

\bigskip 
 

\textbf{LEARNING OBJECTIVES}
 

\begin{itemize}
\item How to connect batteries to obtain different voltage levels
\end{itemize}
\bigskip 
 

