\index{Simulation, computer}
 

This computer simulation is based on the point numbers shown in the previous diagrams for illustrating Kirchhoff's Voltage Law (points 0 through 3).  Resistor values were chosen to provide 50\%, 30\%, and 20\% proportions of total voltage across R$_{1}$, R$_{2}$, and R$_{3}$, respectively.  Feel free to modify the voltage source value (in the "\texttt{.dc}" line, shown here as 6 volts), and/or the resistor values.
 

 

